  "prompt": "How can I get a cast?",
  "response": "To get a cast, you'll typically need to:\n\n1. See a medical professional\n- Visit a doctor, emergency room, or urgent care center\n- Have them examine the injury or condition\n\n2. Get a diagnosis\n- X-rays or other imaging may be needed\n- The doctor will determine if a cast is necessary\n\n3. Cast application\n- A healthcare professional will apply the cast\n- This usually involves:\n  - Cleaning and preparing the area\n  - Padding the limb\n  - Wrapping with plaster or fiberglass\n  - Allowing it to dry and harden\n\nCommon reasons for getting a cast include:\n- Broken bones\n- Severe sprains\n- Some surgical procedures\n- Certain joint or ligament injuries\n\nThe type and duration of the cast will depend on the specific medical condition.",
